ign\n27:   - [ ] sessionPrefix = \"session:\"\n28:   - [ ] expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"\n29:   - [ ] lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"\n30: \n31: **Verification**: Run `go build ./pkg/store` to ensure the implementation compiles and implements the Store interface\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Task 2: Verify Valkey client initialization with proper configuration\n36: - [ ] Verify newValkeyStore function reads VALKEY_ADDR environment variable\n37: - [ ] Verify InitAddress accepts comma-separated addresses (strings.Split)\n38: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD is read correctly\n39: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false allows empty password\n40: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE uses strconv.ParseBool (strict \"true\" check)\n41: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE uses strconv.ParseBool (strict \"true\" check)\n42: - [ ] Verify default addr is \"localhost:6379\" when VALKEY_ADDR not set\n43: - [ ] Verify connection timeout is 5 seconds\n44: - [ ] Verify KeepAlive is 30 seconds\n45: - [ ] Verify Ping succeeds on initialization\n46: \n47: **Verification**: Review newValkeyStore implementation and test with various environment variable combinations\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### Task 3: Verify Ping method implementation\n52: - [ ] Verify Ping uses B().Ping() builder pattern\n53: - [ ] Verify result is converted to string using ToString()\n54: - [ ] Verify \"PONG\" response check\n55: - [ ] Verify error is returned if result != \"PONG\"\n56: - [ ] Verify nil is returned on success\n57: \n58: **Verification**: Test Ping method with healthy Valkey connection\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### Task 4: Verify GetSandboxBySessionID implementation\n63: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n64: - [ ] Verify B().Get().Key(key) builder pattern is used\n65: - [ ] Verify IsValkeyNil() is used to detect empty responses\n66: - [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned for nil responses\n67: - [ ] Verify AsBytes() is used to extract data\n68: - [ ] Verify unmarshalSandboxInfo is called to deserialize JSON\n69: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping with context\n70: \n71: **Verification**: Test GetSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existent sessions\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ### Task 5: Verify StoreSandbox implementation with validation\n76: - [ ] Verify nil sandboxStore validation returns error\n77: - [ ] Verify empty SessionID validation returns error\n78: - [ ] Verify zero ExpiresAt validation returns error\n79: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n80: - [ ] Verify marshalSandboxInfo is called to serialize JSON\n81: - [ ] Verify B().Set().Key().Value().Nx() builder pattern for SETNX\n82: - [ ] Verify B().Zadd().Key().Member().Score() for expiry index with ExpiresAt.Unix()\n83: - [ ] Verify B().Zadd().Key().Member().Score() for last activity index with time.Now().Unix()\n84: - [ ] Verify all three commands are executed (currently using sequential loop, may need DoMulti)\n85: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping for all operations\n86: \n87: **Verification**: Test StoreSandbox with valid data, nil data, empty sessionID, and zero ExpiresAt\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### Task 6: Verify UpdateSandbox implementation with validation\n92: - [ ] Verify nil sandboxStore validation returns error\n93: - [ ] Verify empty SessionID validation returns error\n94: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n95: - [ ] Verify marshalSandboxInfo is called to serialize JSON\n96: - [ ] Verify B().Set().Key().Value().Xx() builder pattern for SETXX\n97: - [ ] Verify result is checked using ToString() == \"OK\"\n98: - [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned if result != \"OK\"\n99: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n100: \n101: **Verification**: Test UpdateSandbox with existing and non-existent sessions, nil data, and empty sessionID\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Task 7: Verify DeleteSandboxBySessionID implementation\n106: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n107: - [ ] Verify B().Del().Key() builder pattern for main key deletion\n108: - [ ] Verify B().Zrem().Key().Member() for expiry index removal\n109: - [ ] Verify B().Zrem().Key().Member() for last activity index removal\n110: - [ ] Verify all three commands are executed (currently using sequential loop, may need DoMulti)\n111: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n112: \n113: **Verification**: Test DeleteSandboxBySessionID with existing and non-existent sessions\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ### Task 8: Verify ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n118: - [ ] Verify B().Zrangebyscore() builder pattern is used\n119: - [ ] Verify Min(\"-inf\") is set for lower bound\n120: - [ ] Verify Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())) is set for upper bound\n121: - [ ] Verify Limit(0, limit) is set correctly\n122: - [ ] Verify ToArray() is used to extract results\n123: - [ ] Verify getSandboxesBySessionIDs is called with session IDs\n124: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n125: \n126: **Verification**: Test ListExpiredSandboxes with multiple sessions and different expiry times\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ### Task 9: Verify ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n131: - [ ] Verify B().Zrangebyscore() builder pattern is used on lastActivityIndexKey\n132: - [ ] Verify Min(\"-inf\") is set for lower bound\n133: - [ ] Verify Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())) is set for upper bound\n134: - [ ] Verify Limit(0, limit) is set correctly\n135: - [ ] Verify ToArray() is used to extract results\n136: - [ ] Verify getSandboxesBySessionIDs is called with session IDs\n137: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n138: \n139: **Verification**: Test ListInactiveSandboxes with multiple sessions and different activity times\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ### Task 10: Verify UpdateSessionLastActivity implementation\n144: - [ ] Verify key is constructed as sessionPrefix + sessionID\n145: - [ ] Verify B().Exists().Key() builder pattern is used\n146: - [ ] Verify ToInt64() is used to check existence\n147: - [ ] Verify exists == 1 check (session must exist)\n148: - [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned if exists != 1\n149: - [ ] Verify B().Zadd().Key().Member().Score() for updating last activity\n150: - [ ] Verify score uses at.Unix()\n151: - [ ] Verify proper error wrapping\n152: \n153: **Verification**: Test UpdateSessionLastActivity with existing and non-existent sessions\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ### Task 11: Verify Close method implementation\n158: - [ ] Verify cli.Close() is called\n159: - [ ] Verify nil is returned after closing\n160: \n161: **Verification**: Test Close method and verify connection is properly closed\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Task 12: Verify getSandboxesBySessionIDs helper implementation\n166: - [ ] Verify empty sessionIDs returns empty slice\n167: - [ ] Verify keys are constructed with sessionPrefix\n168: - [ ] Verify B().Mget().Key(keys...) builder pattern is used\n169: - [ ] Verify ToArray() is used to extract results\n170: - [ ] Verify IsValkeyNil() is used to skip nil values\n171: - [ ] Verify AsBytes() is used to extract data\n172: - [ ] Verify unmarshalSandboxInfo is called for each value\n173: - [ ] Verify klog.Warningf is used for errors but processing continues\n174: - [ ] Verify result slice is built correctly\n175: \n176: **Verification**: Test getSandboxesBySessionIDs with multiple session IDs and missing keys\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ### Task 13: Verify singleton pattern supports Valkey\n181: - [ ] Verify valkeyStoreType constant is \"valkey\"\n182: - [ ] Verify initStore() handles valkeyStoreType case\n183: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_ADDR environment variable is read\n184: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD environment variable is read\n185: - [ ] Verify VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false is handled\n186: - [ ] Verify newValkeyStore is called with correct parameters\n187: - [ ] Verify storeInstance is set correctly\n188: \n189: **Verification**: Test singleton initialization with STORE_TYPE=valkey\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: ### Task 14: Add unit tests for Valkey store (if missing)\n194: - [ ] Create test for Ping method\n195:   - [ ] Test successful ping\n196:   - [ ] Test connection failure\n197: - [ ] Create test for GetSandboxBySessionID\n198:   - [ ] Test with existing session\n199:   - [ ] Test with non-existent session\n200:   - [ ] Test with invalid session ID\n201: - [ ] Create test for StoreSandbox\n202:   - [ ] Test with valid data\n203:   - [ ] Test with nil data\n204:   - [ ] Test with empty sessionID\n205:   - [ ] Test with zero ExpiresAt\n206: - [ ] Create test for UpdateSandbox\n207:   - [ ] Test with existing session\n208:   - [ ] Test with non-existent session\n209:   - [ ] Test with nil data\n210:   - [ ] Test with empty sessionID\n211: - [ ] Create test for DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n212:   - [ ] Test with existing session\n213:   - [ ] Test with non-existent session\n214: - [ ] Create test for ListExpiredSandboxes\n215:   - [ ] Test with multiple expired sessions\n216:   - [ ] Test with no expired sessions\n217:   - [ ] Test with limit\n218: - [ ] Create test for ListInactiveSandboxes\n219:   - [ ] Test with multiple inactive sessions\n220:   - [ ] Test with no inactive sessions\n221:   - [ ] Test with limit\n222: - [ ] Create test for UpdateSessionLastActivity\n223:   - [ ] Test with existing session\n224:   - [ ] Test with non-existent session\n225: - [ ] Create test for Close method\n226: \n227: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/store -run TestValkeyStore` to verify all tests pass\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ### Task 15: Add integration tests for Valkey store\n232: - [ ] Create TestValkeyStoreE2E test\n233:   - [ ] Test complete sandbox lifecycle\n234:   - [ ] Test Store -> Get -> Update -> Delete flow\n235:   - [ ] Verify indices are updated correctly\n236:   - [ ] Verify error handling\n237: - [ ] Create TestValkeyStoreConcurrent test\n238:   - [ ] Test concurrent Store operations\n239:   - [ ] Test concurrent Get operations\n240:   - [ ] Test concurrent Update operations\n241:   - [ ] Test concurrent Delete operations\n242: - [ ] Create TestValkeyStoreIndexConsistency test\n243:   - [ ] Verify expiry index consistency\n244:   - [ ] Verify last activity index consistency\n245:   - [ ] Verify index cleanup on deletion\n246: \n247: **Verification**: Run integration tests with real Valkey instance\n248: \n249: ---\n250: \n251: ### Task 16: Verify error handling consistency with Redis implementation\n252: - [ ] Verify ErrNotFound is returned for non-existent keys\n253: - [ ] Verify error messages are consistent with Redis implementation\n254: - [ ] Verify validation errors match Redis implementation patterns\n255: - [ ] Verify all errors are properly wrapped with context\n256: \n257: **Verification**: Compare error handling between store_valkey.go and store_redis.go\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ### Task 17: Verify ZSET score semantics match design\n262: - [ ] Verify expiry index score uses ExpiresAt.Unix() (not time.Now())\n263: - [ ] Verify last activity index uses time.Now().Unix() on StoreSandbox\n264: - [ ] Verify last activity index uses at.Unix() on UpdateSessionLastActivity\n265: - [ ] Verify scores are float64 as required\n266: \n267: **Verification**: Review StoreSandbox and UpdateSessionLastActivity implementations\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ### Task 18: Verify MGET batch loading implementation\n272: - [ ] Verify MGET is used in getSandboxesBySessionIDs\n273: - [ ] Verify comment about slot requirement is present (for cluster deployments)\n274: - [ ] Verify error handling for batch operations\n275: - [ ] Verify nil value skipping is correct\n276: \n277: **Verification**: Review getSandboxesBySessionIDs implementation and add comment if missing\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ### Task 19: Verify Valkey-specific behaviors\n282: - [ ] Verify IsValkeyNil() is used for nil detection (not redis.Nil)\n283: - [ ] Verify ToString() == \"OK\" check for operation success\n284: - [ ] Verify builder pattern B() is used for all commands\n285: - [ ] Verify DoMulti or sequential loop for atomic operations (document choice)\n286: \n287: **Verification**: Review all Valkey API calls and verify correct usage\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ### Task 20: Run full test suite and verify code quality\n292: - [ ] Run all tests: `go test ./pkg/store -v`\n293:   - [ ] Verify Valkey tests pass\n294:   - [ ] Verify Redis tests still pass (regression check)\n295:   - [ ] Verify singleton tests pass\n296: - [ ] Run static analysis: `go vet ./pkg/store`\n297:   - [ ] Fix any warnings or errors\n298: - [ ] Run linter if configured\n299:   - [ ] Fix any linting issues\n300: - [ ] Run gofmt: `gofmt -s -w ./pkg/store`\n301:   - [ ] Ensure code is properly formatted\n302: - [ ] Update go.mod: `go mod tidy`\n303:   - [ ] Verify valkey-go dependency is present\n304: - [ ] Build package: `go build ./pkg/store`\n305:   - [ ] Verify all packages build successfully\n306: \n307: **Verification**: All tests pass, code is linted, packages build successfully\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Task 21: Update documentation\n312: - [ ] Update pkg/store/README.md (if exists) with Valkey information\n313:   - [ ] Document STORE_TYPE=valkey configuration\n314:   - [ ] Document VALKEY_ADDR, VALKEY_PASSWORD environment variables\n315:   - [ ] Document optional VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE and VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\n316:   - [ ] Document Valkey cluster considerations (MGET slot requirement)\n317:   - [ ] Add usage examples\n318: - [ ] Add inline code comments if needed\n319:   - [ ] Document Valkey-specific behaviors\n320:   - [ ] Document design choices (e.g., sequential vs DoMulti)\n321: - [ ] Update CHANGE.md status to Completed\n322: - [ ] Update delta-spec with implementation notes if needed\n323: \n324: **Verification**: Review documentation for completeness and accuracy\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ## Summary\n329: \n330: **Total Tasks**: 21\n331: **Estimated Effort**: S (Small) - 4-6 hours\n332: \n333: ### Key Deliverables\n334: 1. **Valkey Sto